  "text": "holds for all x ∈ (C \\ D)(K ), for all number fields K of degree n. To define the terms, let C be a regular proper model of C over Spec(O K ). For a point x ∈ C(Q alg ) denote by F a minimal subfield of Q alg over which x is defined. Let s x : Spec(O F ) −→ C be the section uniquely determined by x. Then the height of x associated to a line bundle B on C can be explicitly defined in several equivalent ways (up to a bounded function on C(Q alg )), for instance, by using the canonical height on some projective space into which C is embedded, or as deg(s * x B), where B is an extension to C of B viewed as an arithmetic line bundle on C, cf. sect. 1 of [CITATION_1] or part B of [CITATION_2] . Define log-cond",
